differences in the age progression of mortality between counties, but there were 
significant spatial differences in the level of mortality. The mortality level 
showed a relationship with socioeconomic and health care indicators with the 
expected sign, but with different strengths.
DISCUSSION AND CONCLUSION: The COVID-19 pandemic in 2021 resulted in a decline 
in life expectancy in Hungary not seen since World War II. The study highlights 
the importance of healthcare in addition to social vulnerability. It also points 
out that understanding age patterns will help to mitigate the consequences of 
the epidemic. Orv Hetil. 2023; 164(17): 643-650.

Publisher: Bevezetés: A legtöbb országban a COVID–19-mortalitás az életkor 
